The paper addresses the problem of bug triage in software development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also discusses the use of text classification techniques (cs.IR) and predictive modeling (cs.LG) to reduce the scale and improve the quality of bug data. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and data processing (cs.SI) to achieve their goals.
